        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This looks good, are you up for writing a test? Doesn't need to be complex, just something that actually exercises the code. Probably `test/functional/editor/completion_spec.lua` is the right place.\r\n\r\nYou can [run the test](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/test/README.md#filter-by-file) like this:\r\n\r\n    make functionaltest TEST_FILE=test/functional/editor/completion_spec.lua\r\n\r\nHere is a test stub that should be enough to getting started:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/test/functional/editor/completion_spec.lua b/test/functional/editor/completion_spec.lua\r\nindex 51d2ba675537..9e0c0ef0fedb 100644\r\n--- a/test/functional/editor/completion_spec.lua\r\n+++ b/test/functional/editor/completion_spec.lua\r\n@@ -30,6 +30,16 @@ describe('completion', function()\r\n     }\r\n   end)\r\n \r\n+  it('ctrl-x_ctrl-f completeds Windows drive letter', function()\r\n+    if not t.is_os('win') then\r\n+      return\r\n+    end\r\n+    feed('C:/f<C-x><C-f>')\r\n+    screen:expect{\r\n+      any = [[x]],\r\n+    }\r\n+  end)\r\n+\r\n   describe('v:completed_item', function()\r\n     it('is empty dict until completion', function()\r\n       eq({}, eval('v:completed_item'))\r\n```",
